</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C300A1C2795EFF92BEF47CCBC9E0FC63" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA5F249795EFF92BEF47CCBC9E0FC63" blockId="7.[151,1436,500,957]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795EFF92BEF47CCBC92CFD26" bold="true" box="[197,348,734,760]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795EFF92BF567CCACABEFD26" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[359,718,735,760]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanothorax" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795EFF92BF567CCACABEFD26" box="[359,718,735,760]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">Macrostomus melanothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795EFF92BCD37CCBCB5BFD26" bold="true" box="[738,811,734,760]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25D9320795EFF92BCD37CCBCB5BFD26" box="[738,811,734,760]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
appears close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795EFF92BA217CCACD1BFD27" authority="(Fabricius)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[1040,1387,735,761]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrugineus">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795EFF92BA217CCACCA0FD26" box="[1040,1232,735,760]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">M. ferrugineus</emphasis>
(Fabricius)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795EFF92BB4A7CCAC950FCC1" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscithorax" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795EFF92BB4A7CCAC950FCC1" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">M. fuscithorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795EFF92BF017D10C906FCC1" bold="true" box="[304,374,773,799]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25D9320795EFF92BF017D10C906FCC1" box="[304,374,773,799]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795EFF92BF827D13CA18FCC1" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[435,616,774,799]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusciventris" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795EFF92BF827D13CA18FCC1" box="[435,616,774,799]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">M. fusciventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795EFF92BC487D10CACFFCC1" bold="true" box="[633,703,773,799]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25D9320795EFF92BC487D10CACFFCC1" box="[633,703,773,799]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
on the basis of the acute distal projection of male tergite 8. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795EFF92BEA67D39C99BFC9B" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[151,491,812,837]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanothorax">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795EFF92BEA67D39C99BFC9B" box="[151,491,812,837]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">Macrostomus melanothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares a black thorax with 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795EFF92BD0C7D39CB9FFC9B" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[829,1007,812,837]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscithorax">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795EFF92BD0C7D39CB9FFC9B" box="[829,1007,812,837]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">M. fuscithorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in contrast with the other species, which have a predominantly yellow thorax. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795EFF92BD727D46CB9DFCB2" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[835,1005,851,876]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscithorax">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795EFF92BD727D46CB9DFCB2" box="[835,1005,851,876]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">M. fuscithorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by vein CuA 
<subScript id="179EF00C795EFF92BAB97D76CCE0FCAF" attach="left" box="[1160,1168,867,881]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">1</subScript>
being longer than vein dm-cu, by the shape of the posterior cercus and apex of the epandrium, and by the hypandrium with its thinner and more acute apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
